---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Icon from '../../../components/Icon.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import sujet1 from '../../../assets/images/ferienwohnungsverein-jungfrau-sujet-1.jpg';
import sujet6 from '../../../assets/images/ferienwohnungsverein-jungfrau-sujet-6.jpg';

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Does the 90-day rule of the Airbnb initiative solve the housing shortage?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Experience from other cities shows: not reliably. New York effectively banned short-term rentals (listings -92%) — rents kept rising regardless, and vacancy rates did not improve. We instead propose a model already proven in Wilderswil: a primary-residence quota plus a minimum stay duration, rather than a rigid day cap.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do short-term hosts earn four times a normal rent?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'No. Running a holiday apartment involves substantial work: round-the-clock guest care, cleaning, laundry, replacing and renovating furnishings. This work is not free. Rental income is not simply "profit" but a mix of rent, labour compensation, and cost coverage (e.g. for laundry service, restocking supplies, and other overheads).',
      },
    },
  ],
};
---

<Layout
  title="Our Proposal - Ferienwohnungsverein Jungfrau"
  description="We acknowledge the population's housing concerns – and show a better path than the 90-day rule: the proven Wilderswil model."
  langAlt="/unser-vorschlag/"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section page-hero hero--intro">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>We Offer to Help</h1>
      <p>Our position on short-term rentals – and our proposal for a better solution.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wilderswil model -->
  <section class="section section--white" id="wilderswil">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>The Wilderswil Model: A Village in Our Region Showed the Way</h2>
        <p>In 2025, Wilderswil's population adopted its own solution with <strong>83.5% approval</strong>: a 70% primary-residence quota in all zones, combined with a minimum stay of 5 nights instead of a rigid day cap. The SP subsequently withdrew its own initiative.</p>
        <ul class="icon-list">
          <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span>Protects housing where new building or conversion happens.</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span>Lets holiday apartment hosts keep operating – with clear rules instead of a de facto ban.</span></li>
          <li><Icon name="check-square" size={24} /><span>Was broadly adopted – not only by one political side.</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Our proposal:</strong> we advocate that the remaining Bödeli municipalities examine a model along these lines.</p>
      </div>
      <Image src={sujet1} alt="" width={1024} height={768} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What other cities show -->
  <section class="section section--subtle">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Other Cities and Countries Show</h2>
      <div class="grid-2 spacer-top">
        <div>
          <h3>New York: A Ban Alone Does Not Lower Rents</h3>
          <p>In 2023, New York's "Local Law 18" effectively ended commercial short-term rentals – listings dropped by about 92%. Rents kept rising regardless, and vacancy rates did not improve. The city itself counters that thousands of illegal rentals were eliminated.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Even Strict Rules Often Fail on Enforcement</h3>
          <p>The city of Bern passed a strict rule for its old town in 2022 with 81% approval – it is still not in force today, blocked by a legal challenge. In canton Geneva, an analysis found around 44% of affected hosts violate the existing 90-day rule.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="spacer-top"><strong>A rule is only as good as its enforcement.</strong> That is exactly why we advocate for practical, enforceable solutions rather than rules that sound strict on paper but nobody can enforce.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Facts and figures -->
  <section class="section section--white" id="facts">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <Image src={sujet6} alt="" width={683} height={1024} />
      <div>
        <h2>Facts and Figures</h2>
        <p>Housing units in Interlaken, Unterseen, Matten, Wilderswil, and Bönigen combined:</p>
        <table class="stats-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Category</th><th>Number</th><th>Share</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Housing units total</td><td>12,475</td><td>100%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Primary residences</td><td>10,270</td><td>82.3%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Second homes</td><td>2,205</td><td>17.7%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="quelle">Source: <a href="https://www.are.admin.ch/de/wohnungsinventar">are.admin.ch (housing inventory)</a></p>
        <ul class="icon-list">
          <li>
            <Icon name="arrow-circle-right-solid" size={30} />
            <span>Note that hotels also list some rooms via Airbnb. These are <strong>not</strong> second homes.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <Icon name="arrow-circle-right-solid" size={30} />
            <span>Not every second home is rented short-term: official statistics don't distinguish between privately used and short-term-rented holiday apartments.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="spacer-top-sm">How many second homes are actually rented short-term varies a lot from municipality to municipality: according to <a href="https://www.sab.ch/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Aktuelle-Ansaetze-zur-Regulierung-von-Airbnb_Version-2.pdf">an analysis by the Swiss Association for Mountain Regions (SAB, based on AirDNA data, as of December 2024)</a>, the Airbnb share of the housing stock in <strong>Interlaken is 9.7%</strong> – in other tourism municipalities in the region, it's sometimes much higher (Grindelwald 9.4%, Lauterbrunnen 23.3%). Differences like these are exactly why municipality-specific solutions make more sense than one uniform rule for everyone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quality label -->
  <section class="section section--subtle">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Our Contribution: The Quality Label</h2>
      <p class="lead">We want to earn the trust of guests, neighbours, and municipalities. That's why efforts are under way to build a quality label for responsible holiday apartment hosts – our answer to legitimate criticism: not defensiveness, but taking responsibility. Various ideas are currently being examined, for example:</p>
      <div class="grid-3 quality-points">
        <div>
          <Icon name="check-square" size={48} class="role-icon" />
          <h3>Neighbourhood Standards</h3>
          <p>Clear rules for consideration towards neighbours.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <Icon name="user" size={48} class="role-icon" />
          <h3>Local Contact Persons</h3>
          <p>Designated, reachable contacts for guests and neighbours.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <Icon name="check-square" size={48} class="role-icon" />
          <h3>Controls</h3>
          <p>Verification of standards, not just self-declaration.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a href="/en/membership/" class="btn btn-accent">More about membership</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- National development -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The National Development</h2>
      <p>The federal government is currently preparing (SECO/SEM, as of January 2025) a nationwide, unified registration scheme for short-term rentals – modelled on a new EU regulation. The hotel association HotellerieSuisse likewise calls for a "level playing field" instead of a patchwork of municipal rules. <strong>We support this development</strong> – a proportionate, nationwide solution is better than five different rules across five neighbouring Bödeli municipalities packed into a very small space.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Arguments in detail (FAQ) -->
  <section class="section page-hero" id="arguments">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="grid-2 faq-cards">
        <div class="faq-card">
          <p class="quote-heading"><Icon name="angle-double-right" size={26} /> Does the 90-day rule solve the housing shortage?</p>
          <p>Experience from other cities shows: not reliably. New York effectively banned short-term rentals – rents kept rising regardless, and vacancy rates did not improve.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-card">
          <p class="quote-heading"><Icon name="angle-double-right" size={26} /> Do short-term hosts earn four times a normal rent?</p>
          <p>No. Running a holiday apartment involves substantial work: round-the-clock guest care, cleaning, laundry, replacing and renovating furnishings. This work is not free. Rental income is not simply "profit" but a mix of rent, labour compensation, and cost coverage (e.g. for laundry service, restocking supplies, and other overheads).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="closing-cta">
        <h2>We Don't Want to Be Blockers.</h2>
        <p>Switzerland has a real housing shortage – we don't dispute that. At the same time, our region depends on tourism. We want to show that there is a way to protect housing <strong>and</strong> keep our region a vibrant host to visitors. Wilderswil showed the way. We're ready to help build it.</p>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a href="/en/about-us/" class="btn btn-accent">About Us</a>
          <a href="/en/for-municipalities-media/" class="btn btn-accent">For Municipalities &amp; Media</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero__actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .page-hero p,
  .section--subtle p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .grid-2 h2, .grid-2 h3 { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }

  .lead {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }


  .quality-points {
    margin-block: var(--space-4);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .quality-points h3 {
    margin-block: var(--space-2) var(--space-1);
  }

  .quality-points p {
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .faq-title {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .faq-cards {
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .faq-card {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-3);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  }

  .faq-card .quote-heading {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }

  .faq-card p:not(.quote-heading) {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .closing-cta {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .closing-cta p {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .closing-cta .hero__actions {
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .stats-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-block: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .stats-table th {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .stats-table td {
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .stats-table tbody tr:nth-child(even) {
    background: var(--color-bg-subtle);
  }

  .quelle {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .icon-list {
    margin-block: var(--space-2);
  }

  .quote-heading {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-white);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .spacer-top {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .spacer-top-sm {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
